# Patch for CVE-2026-27942
# Fix stack overflow in XMLBuilder when using preserveOrder:true with non-array input
#
# The vulnerability allows an attacker to crash the application with a stack
# overflow by supplying input to XMLBuilder where a tag value is a non-array
# (e.g. a string, number, boolean, or null). The arrToStr() function in
# orderedJs2Xml.js recursively called itself without a base case for non-array
# values, causing unbounded recursion and a stack overflow.
#
# Fix: Add an explicit non-array guard at the top of arrToStr() that returns
# the value's string representation directly, bypassing the recursive path.
#
# Severity: high (CVSS 3.1: 7.5)
# Affected versions: < 4.5.4, 5.0.0 - 5.3.7
# Fixed in: 5.3.8
# Upstream commit: https://github.com/NaturalIntelligence/fast-xml-parser/commit/c13a961910f14986295dd28484eee830fa1a0e8a
# Advisory: https://github.com/NaturalIntelligence/fast-xml-parser/security/advisories/GHSA-fj3w-jwp8-x2g3

